title.narrative: 2.5: NURTURING CARE AND POSITIVE DESCIPLINE TO CHILDREN

description.narrative: Output 2.5: Social & Behavioural Change Communication (cross-cutting)Parents and caregivers in targeted areas have enhanced skills and social support needed to provide nurturing care and positive discipline to their children., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Empowerment (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Survival and early developmentBy 2022, more vulnerable children in their early years (aged 0 to 6) have improved survival and are nurtured and stimulated for improved early childhood development.

description.narrative: In 2020 UNICEF operationalized the Behavioral Change Communication Model on parenting focusing on media and community engagement in addition to building individual and service providers skills and establishing information systems, which resulted in 130,000 between children, parents, and community members reached with face to face engagement with content related to play-based learning, fatherhood, parenting, hygiene, nutrition and COVID 19 prevention and mitigation of secondary consequences. 53.1 million people reached and 2.5 million engaged through social media campaigns in partnership with MoHP and WHO to support the RCCE strategy in the response of COVID 19. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/12/2019
